{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b87a8578-9f28-49a5-ac20-53fc312ac574","content":"Here's the step-by-step plan:\n\n---\n\n## Building MAUI for Android on Headless Linux CI\n\n### 1. Install the MAUI Workload\n\n```bash\n# Use .NET 10 (your stable SDK)\ndotnet workload install maui-android --sdk-version 10.0.201\n```\n\n### 2. Find the Required Android SDK/NDK Versions\n\nThe MAUI workload pins specific versions. Query them:\n\n```bash\n# Shows the Android API level, build-tools, and NDK version MAUI expects\ndotnet workload list\ngrep -r \"AndroidSdkApiLevel\\|AndroidNdkVersion\\|BuildToolsVersion\" \\\n  /usr/share/dotnet/packs/Microsoft.Android.Sdk.*/\n```\n\nOr check the `WorkloadManifest.json` under:\n`/usr/share/dotnet/sdk-manifests/<band>/microsoft.net.sdk.android/`\n\n### 3. Install Java (JDK 17)\n\n```bash\nsudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install -y openjdk-17-jdk\nexport JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-17-openjdk-amd64\n```\n\n### 4. Install Android Command-Line Tools\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p ~/android-sdk/cmdline-tools\ncd ~/android-sdk/cmdline-tools\ncurl -o tools.zip https://dl.google.com/android/repository/commandlinetools-linux-11076708_latest.zip\nunzip tools.zip && mv cmdline-tools latest\nexport ANDROID_HOME=~/android-sdk\nexport PATH=\"$ANDROID_HOME/cmdline-tools/latest/bin:$PATH\"\n```\n\n### 5. Accept Licenses & Install Exact Components\n\nUse the versions you found in step 2 (example values shown):\n\n```bash\nyes | sdkmanager --licenses\nsdkmanager \\\n  \"platform-tools\" \\\n  \"platforms;android-35\" \\\n  \"build-tools;35.0.0\"\n```\n\n### 6. Set Environment Variables\n\n```bash\nexport ANDROID_HOME=~/android-sdk\nexport JAVA_HOME=/usr/lib/jvm/java-17-openjdk-amd64\n```\n\n### 7. Build\n\n```bash\ndotnet build -f net10.0-android -c Release \\\n  /p:AndroidSdkDirectory=$ANDROID_HOME\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Tips\n\n- **Version discovery is critical** — always derive `platforms;android-XX` and `build-tools` versions from the installed MAUI workload manifest, not from external docs (they go stale).\n- **No emulator/GUI needed** — headless builds only need JDK + SDK command-line tools + platform + build-tools.\n- **CI caching** — cache `~/android-sdk` and `~/.dotnet/workloads` between runs to speed things up.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"203ddc8a-a9b8-449f-bea1-59b15cd6f1c8","outputTokens":699,"requestId":"142C:29F7F6:6A10C69:7264E54:6A03CC8D"},"id":"48e7483c-65f0-450d-9055-5411f115cf0c","timestamp":"2026-05-13T00:58:06.001Z","parentId":"787935de-5858-46a6-bb0a-098056bc44a2"}
